name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Item 1 BUSINESS Overview As our founders Larry and Sergey wrote in the original founders' letter, "Google is not a conventional company.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We do not intend to become one."

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: That unconventional spirit has been a driving force throughout our history -- inspiring us to do things like rethink the mobile device ecosystem with Android and map the world with Google Maps.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As part of that, our founders also explained that you could expect us to make "smaller bets in areas that might seem very speculative or even strange when compared to our current businesses."

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: From the start, the company has always strived to do more, and to do important and meaningful things with the resources we have.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet is a collection of businesses -- the largest of which, of course, is Google.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: It also includes businesses that are generally pretty far afield of our main Internet products such as Access, Calico, CapitalG, GV, Nest, Verily, Waymo, and X.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We report all non-Google businesses collectively as Other Bets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our Alphabet structure is about helping each of our businesses prosper through strong leaders and independence.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Access and technology for everyone The Internet is one of the world's most powerful equalizers, and we see it as our job to make it available to as many people as possible.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: At its core, Google has always been an information company.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We believe that technology is a democratizing force, empowering people through information.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We are helping people get online by tailoring hardware and software experiences that suit the needs of emerging markets, primarily through Android and Chrome.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We're also making sure our core Google products are fast and useful, especially for users in areas where speed and connectivity are central concerns.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other Alphabet companies are also pursuing initiatives with similar goals.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Moonshots Many companies get comfortable doing what they have always done, making only incremental changes.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This incrementalism leads to irrelevance over time, especially in technology, where change tends to be revolutionary, not evolutionary.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: People thought we were crazy when we acquired YouTube and Android and when we launched Chrome, but those efforts have matured into major platforms for digital video and mobile devices and a safer, popular browser.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to look toward the future and continue to invest for the long-term.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We won't become complacent, relying solely on small tweaks.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As we said in the original founders' letter, we will not shy away from high-risk, high-reward projects that we believe in because they are the key to our long-term success.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The power of machine learning Across the company, machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI) are increasingly driving many of our latest innovations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Within Google, our investments in machine learning over a decade are what have enabled us to build Google products that get better over time, making them smarter and more useful -- it's what allows you to use your voice to search for information, to translate the web from one language to another, to see better YouTube recommendations, and to search for people and events that are important to you in Google Photos.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Machine learning is also showing great promise in helping us tackle big issues, like dramatically improving the energy efficiency of our data centers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Across Other Bets, machine learning helps self-driving cars better detect and respond to others on the road, and can also aid clinicians in detecting diabetic retinopathy.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google Serving our users We have always been a company committed to making big bets that have the potential to improve the lives of millions of people.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As the majority of Alphabet's big bets continue to reside within Google, an important benefit of the shift to Alphabet has been the tremendous focus that we're able to have on Google's many extraordinary opportunities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our innovations in areas like search and advertising have made our services widely used, and our brand one of the most recognized in the world.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generate revenues primarily by delivering online advertising that consumers find relevant and that advertisers find cost-effective.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google's core products such as Search, Android, Maps, Chrome, YouTube, Google Play, and Gmail each have over one billion monthly active users.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: But most important, we believe we are just beginning to scratch the surface.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our vision is to remain a place of incredible creativity and innovation that uses our technical expertise to tackle big problems.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google's mission to organize the world's information and make it universally accessible and useful has always been our North Star, and our products have come a long way since the company was founded nearly two decades

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: ago.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We used to show just ten blue links in our results, which you had to click through to find your answers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Now we are increasingly able to provide direct answers -- even if you're speaking your question using Voice Search -- which makes it quicker, easier and more natural to find what you're looking for.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also introduced the Google Assistant, which allows you to type or talk with Google in a natural conversational way to help you get things done.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Over time, we have also added other services that let you access information quickly and easily -- like Google Maps, which helps you navigate to a store while showing you current traffic conditions, or Google Photos, which helps you store and organize all of your photos.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This drive to make information more accessible has led us over the years to improve the discovery and creation of digital content, on the web and through platforms like Google Play and YouTube.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: And with the migration to mobile, people are consuming more digital content by watching more videos, playing more games, listening to more music, reading more books, and using more apps than ever before.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Fueling all of these great digital experiences are powerful platforms and hardware.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: That's why we continue to invest in platforms like our Chrome browser, Android mobile operating system, Chrome operating system, and Daydream virtual reality platform, as well as a new family of great hardware devices like the Pixel phone and Google Home.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google was a company built in the cloud and has been investing in infrastructure, data management, analytics, and AI from the very beginning.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We've taken those long-term investments and offer many of the same cloud services to our enterprise customers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Because more and more of today's great digital experiences are being built in the cloud, our enterprise cloud products help businesses of all sizes take advantage of the latest technology advances to operate more efficiently.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: How we make money The goal of our advertising business is to deliver relevant ads at just the right time and to give people useful commercial information, regardless of the device they're using.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also provide advertisers with tools that help them better attribute and measure their advertising campaigns across screens.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our advertising solutions help millions of companies grow their businesses, and we offer a wide range of products across screens and devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generate revenues primarily by delivering both performance advertising and brand advertising.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Performance advertising creates and delivers relevant ads that users will click on, leading to direct engagement with advertisers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Most of our performance advertisers pay us when a user engages in their ads.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Performance advertising lets our advertisers connect with users while driving measurable results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For performance advertisers, AdWords, our primary auction-based advertising program, helps create simple text-based ads that appear on Google properties and the properties of Google Network Members.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, Google Network Members use our AdSense program to display relevant ads on their properties, generating revenues when site visitors view or click on the ads.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to invest in our advertising programs and make significant upgrades.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Brand advertising helps enhance users' awareness of and affinity with advertisers' products and services, through videos, text, images, and other interactive ads that run across various devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We help brand advertisers deliver digital videos and other types of ads to specific audiences for their brand-building marketing campaigns.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have built a world-class ad technology platform for brand advertisers, agencies, and publishers to power their digital marketing businesses.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We aim to ensure great user experiences by serving the right ads at the right time and by building deep partnerships with brands and agencies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also seek to improve the measurability of brand advertising so advertisers know when their campaigns are effective.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Furthermore, we have invested significantly in programmatic advertising to help advertisers reach users when and where it matters through automated ad buying, giving them access to top-tier inventory across screens and formats, as well as the real-time insights that advertisers need to make their buys count.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have allocated substantial resources to stopping bad advertising practices and protecting users on the web.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We focus on creating the best advertising experiences for our users and advertisers in many ways, ranging from removing hundreds of millions of bad ads from our systems every year to closely monitoring the sites and apps that show our ads and blacklisting them when necessary to ensure that our ads do not fund bad content.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Beyond our advertising business, we also generate revenues in emerging areas, such as digital content, cloud services, and hardware.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other Bets Throughout Alphabet, we are also using technology to try and solve big problems across many industries.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet's Other Bets are early-stage businesses, which come with considerable uncertainty, but they are already making important strides in their industries.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our goal is for them to become thriving, successful businesses in the medium to long term.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For instance, Nest products, led by their learning thermostat, remain top sellers in their categories, and the team continues to successfully launch new products like the Nest Cam Outdoor.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Also, life sciences and healthcare company Verily has forged several partnerships with industry leaders as it works to create new solutions in areas including diabetes and robotic surgery.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our self-driving car company, Waymo, is also making important progress and is currently testing cars in four cities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to build out these businesses thoughtfully and systematically to capitalize on the opportunities ahead.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Competition Our business is characterized by rapid change as well as new and disruptive technologies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We face formidable competition in every aspect of our business, particularly from companies that seek to connect people with online information and provide them with relevant advertising.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We face competition from:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • General purpose search engines and information services, such as Microsoft's Bing, Yahoo, Yandex, Baidu, Naver, and Seznam.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Vertical search engines and e-commerce websites, such as Amazon and eBay (e-commerce), Kayak (travel queries), LinkedIn (job queries), and WebMD (health queries). Some users will navigate directly to such content, websites, and apps rather than go through Google.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Social networks, such as Facebook and Twitter. Some users are increasingly relying on social networks for product or service referrals, rather than seeking information through traditional search engines.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Other forms of advertising, such as television, radio, newspapers, magazines, and billboards. Our advertisers typically advertise in multiple media, both online and offline.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Other online advertising platforms and networks, including Facebook, Criteo, and AppNexus, that compete for advertisers with AdWords, our primary auction-based advertising program.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Providers of digital video services, such as Facebook, Netflix, Amazon, and Hulu.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Companies that design, manufacture, and market consumer electronics products, including businesses that have developed proprietary platforms.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Providers of enterprise cloud services, including Amazon and Microsoft.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Digital assistant providers, such as Apple, Amazon, Facebook, and Microsoft.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Competing successfully in our advertising-related businesses depends heavily on our ability to deliver and distribute innovative products and technologies to the marketplace so that we can attract and retain:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Users, for whom other products and services are literally one click away, primarily on the basis of the relevance and usefulness of our search results and the features, availability, and ease of use of our products and services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Advertisers, primarily based on our ability to generate sales leads, and ultimately customers, and to deliver their advertisements in an efficient and effective manner across a variety of distribution channels.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Content providers (Google Network Members, the parties who use our advertising programs to deliver relevant ads alongside their search results and content, as well as other content providers for whom we distribute or license content), primarily based on the quality of our advertiser base, our ability to help these partners generate revenues from advertising, and the terms of our agreements with them.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Intellectual Property We rely on various intellectual property laws, confidentiality procedures and contractual provisions to protect our proprietary technology and our brand.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have registered, and applied for the registration of, U.S. and international trademarks service marks, domain names and copyrights.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have also filed patent applications in the U.S. and foreign countries covering certain of our technology, and acquired patent assets to supplement our portfolio.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have licensed in the past, and expect that we may license in the future, certain of our rights to other parties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Culture and Employees We take great pride in our culture.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We embrace collaboration and creativity, and encourage the iteration of ideas to address complex technical challenges.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Transparency and open dialogue are central to how we work, and we like to ensure that company news reaches our employees first through internal channels.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Despite our rapid growth, we still cherish our roots as a startup and wherever possible empower employees to act on great ideas regardless of their role or function within the company.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We strive to hire great employees, with backgrounds and perspectives as diverse as those of our global users.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We work to provide an environment where these talented people can have fulfilling careers addressing some of the biggest challenges in technology and society.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our employees are among our best assets and are critical for our continued success.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We expect to continue investing in hiring talented employees and to provide competitive compensation programs to our employees.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As of December 31, 2016, we had 72,053 full-time employees: 27,169 in research and development, 20,902 in sales and marketing, 14,287 in operations, and 9,695 in general and administrative functions.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Although we have work councils and statutory employee representation obligations in certain countries, our U.S. employees are not represented by a labor union.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Competition for qualified personnel in our industry is intense, particularly for software engineers, computer scientists, and other technical staff.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Seasonality Our business is affected by seasonal fluctuations in Internet usage, advertising expenditures, and underlying business trends such as traditional retail seasonality (e.g., commercial queries typically increase in the fourth quarter of each year).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other Items Climate change is one of the most significant global challenges of our time, and we've long been committed to improving our energy consumption.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In 2012, we set a long term goal to reach 100% renewable energy for our operations, and we expect to achieve that goal in 2017.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to invest in our existing products and services as well as developing new products and services through research and product development.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We often release early-stage products.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We then use data and user feedback to decide if and how to invest further in those products.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Research and development expenses include the vast majority of engineering and technical headcount responsible for research and development of our existing and new products and services, as well as their associated costs.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For more information please refer to the Consolidated Statements of Income included in Part II of this Annual Report on Form 10-K.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For information about segments and geographic areas, please refer to Note 15 of the Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements included in Part II of this Annual Report on Form 10-K.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As part of the Alphabet reorganization, we expect to convert Google Inc. into a limited liability company.

sentence: Available Information Our website is located at www.abc.xyz, and our investor relations website is located at www.abc.xyz/investor.

sentence: Our Annual Reports on Form 10-K, Quarterly Reports on Form 10-Q, and our Proxy Statements are available through our investor relations website, free of charge, after we file them with the SEC.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also provide a link to the section of the SEC's website at www.sec.gov that has all of the reports that we file or furnish with the SEC.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: You may read and copy any materials we file with the SEC at the SEC's Public Reference Room at 100 F Street, NE, Washington, D.C. 20549.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: You can get information on the operation of the Public Reference Room by calling the SEC at 1-800-SEC-0330.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We webcast via our investor relations website our earnings calls and certain events we participate in or host with members of the investment community.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our investor relations website also provides notifications of news or announcements regarding our financial performance, including SEC filings, investor events, press and earnings releases, and blogs.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Further corporate governance information, including our certificate of incorporation, bylaws, governance guidelines, board committee charters, and code of conduct, is also available on our investor relations website under the heading "Other."

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The content of our websites are not incorporated by reference into this Annual Report on Form 10-K or in any other report or document we file with the SEC, and any references to our websites are intended to be inactive textual references only.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Item 1A RISK FACTORS Our operations and financial results are subject to various risks and uncertainties, including but not limited to those described below, which could adversely affect our business, financial condition, results of operations, cash flows, and the trading price of our common and capital stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Risks Related to Our Businesses and Industries We face intense competition.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If we do not continue to innovate and provide products and services that are useful to users, we may not remain competitive, and our revenues and operating results could be adversely affected.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our businesses are rapidly evolving, intensely competitive, and subject to changing technologies, shifting user needs, and frequent introductions of new products and services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Competing successfully depends heavily on our ability to accurately anticipate technology developments and deliver innovative products and technologies to the marketplace rapidly and, for Google, provide products and services that make our search results and ads relevant and useful for our users.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As our businesses evolve, the competitive pressure to innovate will encompass a wider range of products and services, including products and services that may be outside of our historical core business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, we must continue to invest significant resources in research and development, including through acquisitions, in order to enhance our search technology and our existing products and services, and introduce new products and services that people can easily and effectively use.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have many competitors in different industries, including general purpose search engines and information services; vertical search engines and e-commerce websites; social networks; other forms of advertising and online advertising platforms and networks; companies that design, manufacture, and market consumer electronic products; providers of enterprise cloud services and digital video services; and digital assistant providers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our current and potential domestic and international competitors range from large and established companies to emerging start-ups.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Some large companies have longer operating histories and more established relationships with customers and users, and they can use their experiences and resources in ways that could affect our competitive position, including by making acquisitions, continuing to invest heavily in research and development, aggressively initiating intellectual property claims (whether or not meritorious), and continuing to compete aggressively for advertisers and websites.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Emerging start-ups may be able to innovate and provide products and services faster than we can or may foresee the consumer need for products and services before us.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, new products and services can sometimes present new and difficult technological and legal challenges, which may negatively impact our brands and demand for our products and services and adversely impact our revenues and operating results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our operating results would also suffer if our innovations are not responsive to the needs of our users, advertisers, and Google Network Members; are not appropriately timed with market opportunities; or are not effectively brought to market.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As technology continues to develop, our competitors may be able to offer user experiences that are, or that are seen to be, substantially similar to or better than ours.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This may force us to compete in different ways and expend significant resources in order to remain competitive.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If our competitors are more successful than we are in developing compelling products or in attracting and retaining users, advertisers, and content providers, our revenues and operating results could be adversely affected.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generate substantially all of our revenues from advertising, and reduced spending by advertisers or a loss of partners could harm our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We generated 88% of total revenues from advertising in 2016.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Many of our advertisers, companies that distribute our products and services, digital publishers, and content partners can terminate their contracts with us at any time.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Those partners may not continue to do business with us if we do not create more value (such as increased numbers of users or customers, new sales leads, increased brand awareness, or more effective monetization) than their available alternatives.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If we do not provide superior value or deliver advertisements efficiently and competitively, we could see a decrease in revenue and other adverse impacts to our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, expenditures by advertisers tend to be cyclical, reflecting overall economic conditions and budgeting and buying patterns.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Adverse macroeconomic conditions can also have a material negative impact on user activity and the demand for advertising and cause our advertisers to reduce the amounts they spend on advertising, which could adversely affect our revenues and business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our ongoing investment in new businesses and new products, services, and technologies is inherently risky, and could disrupt our current operations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have invested and expect to continue to invest in new businesses, products, services, and technologies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The creation of Alphabet as a new holding company in 2015 and the investments that we are making across various areas in Google and Other Bets are a reflection of our ongoing efforts to innovate and provide products and services that

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: are useful to users.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Such endeavors may involve significant risks and uncertainties, including insufficient revenues from such investments to offset any new liabilities assumed and expenses associated with these new investments, inadequate return of capital on our investments, distraction of management from current operations, use of alternative investment or compensation structures, and unidentified issues not discovered in our due diligence of such strategies and offerings that could cause us to fail to realize the anticipated benefits of such investments and incur unanticipated liabilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Because these new ventures are inherently risky, no assurance can be given that such strategies and offerings will be successful and will not adversely affect our reputation, financial condition, and operating results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: More people are using devices other than desktop computers to access the Internet and accessing new devices to make search queries.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If manufacturers and users do not widely adopt versions of our search technology, products, or operating systems developed for these devices, our business could be adversely affected.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The number of people who access the Internet through devices other than desktop computers, including mobile phones, smartphones, handheld computers such as laptops and tablets, video game consoles, digital assistants, and television set-top devices, is increasing dramatically.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The functionality and user experience associated with some alternative devices may make the use of our products and services through such devices more difficult (or just different) and the versions of our products and services developed for these devices may not be compelling to users, manufacturers, or distributors of alternative devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Each manufacturer or distributor may establish unique technical standards for its devices, and our products and services may not work or be viewable on these devices as a result.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Some manufacturers may also elect not to include our products on their devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, search queries are increasingly being undertaken via "apps" tailored to particular devices or social media platforms, which could affect our search and advertising business over time.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As new devices and platforms are continually being released, it is difficult to predict the problems we may encounter in adapting our products and services and developing competitive new products and services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We expect to continue to devote significant resources to the creation, support, and maintenance of products and services across multiple platforms and devices.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If we are unable to attract and retain a substantial number of alternative device manufacturers, suppliers, distributors, developers, and users to our products and services, or if we are slow to develop products and technologies that are more compatible with alternative devices and platforms, we will fail to capture the opportunities available as consumers and advertisers continue to exist in a dynamic, multi-screen environment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our revenue growth rate could decline over time, and we anticipate downward pressure on our operating margin in the future.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our revenue growth rate could decline over time as a result of a number of factors, including:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • increasing competition, • changes in property mix, platform mix, device mix, and geographical mix,

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • the challenges in maintaining our growth rate as our revenues increase to higher levels,

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • the evolution of the online advertising market, including the increasing variety of online platforms for advertising, and the other markets in which we participate, and

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • the rate of user adoption of our products, services, and technologies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We believe our margins could experience downward pressure as a result of increasing competition and increased costs for many aspects of our business as well as the continuing shift to mobile, changes in device mix, and the contribution of new businesses to overall revenue.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For instance, the margin on revenues we generate from our Google Network Members is significantly less than the margin on revenues we generate from advertising on Google properties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Consequently, our margins will experience downward pressure if a greater percentage of our revenues comes from ads placed on our Google Network Members' properties compared to revenues generated through ads placed on Google properties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, the margin we earn on revenues generated from our Google Network Members could decrease in the future if we pay an even larger percentage of advertising fees to our Google Network Members.

name: Alphabet Inc.

sentence: Risks Related to Ownership of Our Stock The trading price for our Class A common stock and non-voting Class C capital stock may continue to be volatile.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The trading price of our stock has at times experienced substantial price volatility and may continue to be volatile.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For example, from January 1, 2016 through December 31, 2016, the closing price of our Class A common stock ranged from $681.14 per share to $835.74 per share, and the closing price of our Class C capital stock ranged from $668.26 to $813.11 per share.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition to the factors discussed in this Annual Report on Form 10-K, the trading price of our Class A common stock and Class C capital stock may fluctuate widely in response to various factors, many of which are beyond our control, including, among others:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Quarterly variations in our results of operations or those of our competitors.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Announcements by us or our competitors of acquisitions, divestitures, investments, new products, significant contracts, commercial relationships, or capital commitments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Recommendations by securities analysts or changes in earnings estimates.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Announcements about our earnings that are not in line with analyst expectations, the risk of which is enhanced because it is our policy not to give guidance on earnings.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Announcements by our competitors of their earnings that are not in line with analyst expectations.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Commentary by industry and market professionals about our products, strategies, and other matters affecting our business and results, regardless of its accuracy.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • The volume of shares of Class A common stock and Class C capital stock available for public sale.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Sales of Class A common stock and Class C capital stock by us or by our stockholders (including sales by our directors, executive officers, and other employees).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Short sales, hedging, and other derivative transactions on shares of our Class A common stock and Class C capital stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • The perceived values of Class A common stock and Class C capital stock relative to one another.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our stock repurchase program.

sentence: In addition, the stock market in general, and the market for technology companies in particular, have experienced extreme price and volume fluctuations that have often been unrelated or disproportionate to the operating performance of those companies.

name: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The concentration of our stock ownership limits our stockholders' ability to influence corporate matters.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our Class B common stock has 10 votes per share, our Class A common stock has one vote per share, and our Class C capital stock has no voting rights.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As of December 31, 2016, Larry, Sergey, and Eric beneficially owned approximately 92.4% of our outstanding Class B common stock, which represented approximately 56.8% of the voting power of our outstanding capital stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Larry, Sergey, and Eric therefore have significant influence over management and affairs and over all matters requiring stockholder approval, including the election of directors and significant corporate transactions, such as a merger or other sale of our company or our assets, for the foreseeable future.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, because our Class C capital stock carries no voting rights (except as required by applicable law), the issuance of the Class C capital stock, including in future stock-based acquisition transactions and to fund employee equity incentive programs, could prolong the duration of Larry and Sergey's current relative ownership of our voting power and their ability to elect all of our directors and to determine the outcome of most matters submitted to a vote of our stockholders.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Together with Eric, they would also continue to be able to control any required stockholder vote with respect to certain change in control transactions involving Alphabet (including an acquisition of Alphabet by another company).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This concentrated control limits or severely restricts our stockholders' ability to influence corporate matters and, as a result, we may take actions that our stockholders do not view as beneficial.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, the market price of our Class A common stock and our Class C capital stock could be adversely affected.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Provisions in our charter documents and under Delaware law could discourage a takeover that stockholders may consider favorable.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Provisions in Alphabet's certificate of incorporation and bylaws may have the effect of delaying or preventing a change of control or changes in our management. These provisions include the following:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our certificate of incorporation provides for a tri-class capital stock structure.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result of this structure, Larry, Sergey, and Eric have significant influence over all matters requiring stockholder approval, including the election of directors and significant corporate transactions, such as a merger or other sale of our company or our assets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This concentrated control could discourage others from initiating any potential merger, takeover, or other change of control transaction that other stockholders may view as beneficial.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As noted above, the issuance of the Class C capital stock could have the effect of prolonging the influence of Larry, Sergey, and Eric.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our board of directors has the right to elect directors to fill a vacancy created by the expansion of the board of directors or the resignation, death, or removal of a director, which prevents stockholders from being able to fill vacancies on our board of directors.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our stockholders may not act by written consent. As a result, a holder, or holders, controlling a majority of our capital stock would not be able to take certain actions without holding a stockholders' meeting.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our certificate of incorporation prohibits cumulative voting in the election of directors. This limits the ability of minority stockholders to elect director candidates.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Stockholders must provide advance notice to nominate individuals for election to the board of directors or to propose matters that can be acted upon at a stockholders' meeting.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These provisions may discourage or deter a potential acquirer from conducting a solicitation of proxies to elect the acquirer's own slate of directors or otherwise attempting to obtain control of our company.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Our board of directors may issue, without stockholder approval, shares of undesignated preferred stock.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The ability to issue undesignated preferred stock makes it possible for our board of directors to issue preferred stock with voting or other rights or preferences that could impede the success of any attempt to acquire us.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a Delaware corporation, we are also subject to certain Delaware anti-takeover provisions.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Under Delaware law, a corporation may not engage in a business combination with any holder of 15% or more of its outstanding voting stock unless the holder has held the stock for three years or, among other things, the board of directors has approved the transaction.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our board of directors could rely on Delaware law to prevent or delay an acquisition of us.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Risks Related to Our Holding Company Reorganization As a holding company, Alphabet is dependent on the operations and funds of its subsidiaries.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: On October 2, 2015, we completed a reorganization pursuant to which Alphabet became a holding company with no business operations of its own.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet's only significant assets are the outstanding equity interests in Google and any other current or future subsidiaries of Alphabet.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, we rely on cash flows from subsidiaries to meet our obligations, including to service any debt obligations of Alphabet.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We may not obtain the anticipated benefits of our reorganization into a holding company structure.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We believe that our holding company reorganization and the current operating structure increases management scale and allows us to focus on running our diverse businesses independently with the goal of maximizing each of the business' potential.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The benefits of this reorganization may not be obtained if circumstances prevent us from taking advantage of the strategic and business opportunities that we expect it may afford us.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As a result, we may incur the costs of a holding company structure without realizing the benefits, which could adversely affect our reputation, financial condition, and operating results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet's management is dedicating significant effort to the Alphabet operating structure.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These efforts may divert management's focus and resources from Alphabet's business, corporate initiatives, or strategic opportunities, which could have an adverse effect on our businesses, results of operations, financial condition, or prospects.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, our subsidiaries may be restricted in their ability to pay cash dividends or to make other distributions to Alphabet, as the new holding company.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Trends in Our Business The following trends have contributed to the results of our consolidated operations, and we anticipate that they will continue to impact our future results:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •Users' behaviors and advertising continue to shift online as the digital economy evolves.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The continuing shift from an offline to online world has contributed to the growth of our business since inception, resulting in increasing revenues, and we expect that this online shift will continue to benefit our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •As online advertising evolves, we continue to expand our product offerings which may impact our monetization.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: As interactions between users and advertisers change, we continue to expand and evolve our product offerings to serve their changing needs.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Over time, we expect our monetization trends to fluctuate.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For example, we have seen an increase in YouTube engagement ads, which monetize at a lower rate than traditional desktop search ads.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, we continue to see a shift to programmatic buying which presents opportunities for advertisers to connect with the right user, in the right moment, in the right context.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Programmatic buying has a different monetization profile than traditional advertising buying on Google properties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These trends will continue to affect our revenues and margins in the future.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •Users are increasingly using multiple devices to access our products and services, and our advertising revenues are increasingly coming from mobile and other new formats.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our users are accessing the Internet via multiple devices and want to feel connected no matter where they are or what they are doing.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We seek to expand our products and services to stay in front of this shift in order to maintain and grow our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In this multi-device world, we generate our advertising revenues increasingly from mobile and newer advertising formats, and the margins from the advertising revenues from these sources have generally been lower than those from traditional desktop search.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also expect traffic acquisition costs (TAC) paid to our distribution partners to increase due to changes in device mix between mobile, desktop, and tablet, partner mix, partner agreement terms, and the percentage of queries channeled through paid access points.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We expect these trends to continue to put pressure on our overall margins.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •As users in developing economies increasingly come online, our revenues from international markets continue to increase and movements in foreign exchange rates impact such revenues.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The shift to online, as well as the advent of the multi-device world, has brought opportunities outside of the U.S., including in emerging markets, and we continue to develop localized versions of our products and relevant advertising programs useful to our users in these markets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: This has led to a trend of increased revenues from international markets over time and we expect that our results will continue to be impacted by our performance in these markets, particularly as low-cost mobile devices become more available.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our international revenues represent a significant portion of our revenues and are subject to fluctuations in foreign currency exchange rates relative to the U.S. dollar.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: While we have a foreign exchange risk management program designed to reduce our exposure to these fluctuations, this program does not fully offset their effect on our revenues and earnings.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •The portion of our revenues that we derive from non-advertising revenues is increasing.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Non-advertising revenues have grown over time.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We expect this trend to continue as we focus on expanding our Google offerings to our users through products and services like Google Cloud, Google Play, and hardware products.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Across these initiatives, we currently derive non-advertising revenues primarily from hardware sales, sales of apps, in-app purchases and digital content products, and service and licensing fees; the margins on these non-advertising businesses vary significantly and may be lower than the margins on our advertising business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: A number of our Other Bets initiatives are in their initial development stages, and as such, the sources of revenues from these businesses could change over time and the revenues could be volatile.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: •As we continue to look for new ways to serve our users and expand our businesses, we will invest heavily in R&D and our capital expenditures will continue to fluctuate.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We continue to make significant research and development (R&D) investments in areas of strategic focus for Google, such as search, advertising, and machine learning, as well as in new products and services across both Google and Other Bets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The amount of our capital expenditures has fluctuated and may continue to fluctuate in the long term as we invest heavily in our systems, data centers, real estate and facilities, and information technology infrastructure.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, acquisitions remain an important part of our strategy and use of capital, and we expect to continue to spend cash on acquisitions and other investments.

sentence: Executive Overview of Results Here are our key financial results for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2016 (consolidated unless otherwise noted):

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Revenues of $90.3 billion and revenue growth of 20% year over year, constant currency revenue growth of 24% year over year.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Google segment revenues of $89.5 billion with revenue growth of 20% year over year and Other Bets revenues of $0.8 billion with revenue growth of 82% year over year.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Revenues from the United States, the United Kingdom, and Rest of the world were $42.8 billion, $7.8 billion, and $39.7 billion, respectively.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Cost of revenues was $35.1 billion, consisting of traffic acquisition costs of $16.8 billion and other cost of revenues of $18.3 billion. Our traffic acquisition costs as a percentage of advertising revenues was 21%.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Operating expenses (excluding cost of revenues) were $31.4 billion.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Income from operations was $23.7 billion.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Effective tax rate was 19%.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Net income was $19.5 billion with diluted net income per share of $27.85.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Operating cash flow was $36.0 billion.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Capital expenditures were $10.2 billion.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Headcount increased to 72,053 as of December 31, 2016.

sentence: Information about Segments We operate our business in multiple operating segments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google is our only reportable segment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: None of our other segments meet the quantitative thresholds to qualify as reportable segments; therefore, the other operating segments are combined and disclosed below as Other Bets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our reported segments are described below: • Google - Google includes our main internet products such as Search, Ads, Commerce, Maps, YouTube, Google Cloud, Android, Chrome, and Google Play as well as our hardware initiatives.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our technical infrastructure and some newer efforts like virtual reality are also included in Google.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Google generates revenues primarily from advertising, sales of digital content, apps and cloud offerings, and sales of hardware products.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Other Bets - Other Bets is a combination of multiple operating segments that are not individually material.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other Bets includes businesses such as Access, Calico, CapitalG, GV, Nest, Verily, Waymo, and X.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Revenues from the Other Bets are derived primarily through the sales of internet and TV services through Google Fiber, sales of Nest products and services, and licensing and R&D services through Verily.

sentence: Use of Monetization Metrics When assessing our advertising revenue performance, we present information regarding the percentage change in the number of "paid clicks" and "cost-per-click" for our Google properties and Google Network Members' properties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Management views these as important metrics for understanding our business.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We periodically review, refine and update our methodologies for monitoring, gathering, and counting the number of paid clicks and for identifying the revenues generated by click activity.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Paid clicks for our Google properties represent engagement by users and include clicks on advertisements by end-users related to searches on Google.com, clicks related to advertisements on other owned and operated properties including Gmail, Maps, and Google Play; and viewed YouTube engagement ads like TrueView (counted as an engagement when the user chooses not to skip the ad) and certain trial ad formats.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Paid clicks for our Google Network Members' properties include clicks by end-users related to advertisements served on Google Network Members' properties participating in our AdSense for Search, AdSense for Content and AdMob businesses.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In some cases, such as programmatic and reservation based advertising buying, we charge advertisers by impression; while growing, this represents a small part of our revenue base.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Cost-per-click is defined as click-driven revenue divided by our total number of paid clicks and represents the average amount we charge advertisers for each engagement by users.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Revenue growth and the change in revenue growth, as well as the change in paid clicks and cost-per-click on Google properties and Google Network Members' properties and the correlation between these items, has fluctuated and may continue to fluctuate because of various factors, including:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • growth rates of our revenues from Google properties, including YouTube, compared to those of our revenues from Google Network Members' properties;

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • advertiser competition for keywords; • changes in foreign currency exchange rates; • seasonality; Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • the fees advertisers are willing to pay based on how they manage their advertising costs;

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • changes in advertising quality or formats; • changes in device mix; • traffic growth in emerging markets compared to more mature markets and across various advertising verticals and channels;

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • a shift in the proportion of non-click based revenue generated on Google properties and Google Network Members' properties, including an increase in programmatic and reservation based advertising buying; and

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • general economic conditions.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our advertising revenue growth rate has fluctuated over time as a result of a number of factors, including increasing competition, query growth rates, challenges in maintaining our growth rate as our revenues increase to higher levels, the evolution of the online advertising market, our investments in new business strategies, changes in our product mix, and shifts in the geographic mix of our revenues.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We also expect that our revenue growth rate will continue to be affected by evolving user preferences, the acceptance by users of our products and services as they are delivered on diverse devices, our ability to create a seamless experience for both users and advertisers, and movements in foreign currency exchange rates.

name: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Use of Constant Currency Revenues and Constant Currency Revenue Growth

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The impact of currency exchange rates on our business is an important factor in understanding period to period comparisons.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our international revenues are favorably impacted as the U.S. dollar weakens relative to other foreign currencies, and unfavorably impacted as the U.S dollar strengthens relative to other foreign currencies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We use non-GAAP constant currency revenues and constant currency revenue growth for financial and operational decision-making and as a means to evaluate period-to-period comparisons.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We believe the presentation of results on a constant currency basis in addition to GAAP results helps improve the ability to understand our performance because they exclude the effects of foreign currency volatility that are not indicative of our core operating results.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Constant currency information compares results between periods as if exchange rates had remained constant period over period.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We define constant currency revenues as total revenues excluding the impact of foreign exchange rate movements and hedging activities, and use it to determine the constant currency revenue growth on a year-on-year basis.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Constant currency revenues are calculated by translating current period revenues using prior period exchange rates, as well as excluding any hedging impacts realized in the current period.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Constant currency revenue growth (expressed as a percentage) is calculated by determining the increase in current period revenues over prior period revenues where current period foreign currency revenues are translated using prior period exchange rates and hedging benefits are excluded from revenues of both periods.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: These results should be considered in addition to, not as a substitute for, results reported in accordance with GAAP.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Results on a constant currency basis, as we present them, may not be comparable to similarly titled measures used by other companies and are not a measure of performance presented in accordance with GAAP.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In 2016 and in 2015, our revenues from the United Kingdom were unfavorably impacted by changes in foreign currency exchange rates over the prior year, primarily as the British pound weakened relative to the U.S. dollar.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In 2016, our revenues from the Rest of the world (excluding the United Kingdom) were unfavorably impacted by changes in foreign currency exchange rates, primarily because the U.S. dollar strengthened relative to certain currencies including the Euro and Argentine peso, partially offset by the impact of the U.S. dollar weakening relative to the Japanese yen.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In 2015, our revenues from the Rest of the world (excluding the United Kingdom) were unfavorably impacted by changes in foreign currency exchange rates, primarily because the U.S. dollar strengthened relative to the Euro, Brazilian real, Australian dollar, and Japanese yen.

sentence: Consolidated Costs and Expenses Cost of Revenues Cost of revenues consists of traffic acquisition costs (TAC) which are paid to Google Network Members primarily for ads displayed on their properties and amounts paid to our distribution partners who make available our search access points and services.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Our distribution partners include browser providers, mobile carriers, original equipment manufacturers, and software developers.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Additionally, other cost of revenues (which is the cost of revenues excluding traffic acquisition costs) includes the following:

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • The expenses associated with the operation of our data centers (including depreciation, labor, energy, bandwidth, and other equipment costs);

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Content acquisition costs primarily related to payments to certain content providers from whom we license their video and other content for distribution on YouTube and Google Play (we pay fees to these content providers based on revenues generated or a flat fee);

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Credit card and other transaction fees related to processing customer transactions;

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: • Stock-based compensation expense; • Inventory related costs for hardware we sell; and • Amortization of certain intangible assets.

name: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Critical Accounting Policies and Estimates We prepare our consolidated financial statements in accordance with U.S. Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP).

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In doing so, we have to make estimates and assumptions that affect our reported amounts of assets, liabilities, revenues, and expenses, as well as related disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In some cases, we could reasonably have used different accounting policies and estimates.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In some cases, changes in the accounting estimates are reasonably likely to occur from period to period.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Accordingly, actual results could differ materially from our estimates.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: To the extent that there are material differences between these estimates and actual results, our financial condition or results of operations will be affected.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We base our estimates on past experience and other assumptions that we believe are reasonable under the circumstances, and we evaluate these estimates on an ongoing basis.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We refer to accounting estimates of this type as critical accounting policies and estimates, which we discuss further below.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We have reviewed our critical accounting policies and estimates with the audit committee of our board of directors.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Please see Note 1 of Part II, Item 8 of this Annual Report on Form 10-K for the summary of significant accounting policies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Income Taxes We are subject to income taxes in the U.S. and numerous foreign jurisdictions. Significant judgment is required in evaluating our uncertain tax positions and determining our provision for income taxes.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Although we believe we have adequately reserved for our uncertain tax positions, no assurance can be given that the final tax outcome of these matters will not be different.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We adjust these reserves in light of changing facts and circumstances, such as the closing of a tax audit or the refinement of an estimate.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: To the extent that the final tax outcome of these matters is different than the amounts recorded, such differences will impact the provision for income taxes and the effective tax rate in the period in which such determination is made.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The provision for income taxes includes the impact of reserve provisions and changes to reserves that are considered appropriate, as well as the related net interest and penalties.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: In addition, we are subject to the continuous examination of our income tax returns by the IRS and other tax authorities which may assert assessments against us.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We regularly assess the likelihood of adverse outcomes resulting from these examinations and assessments to determine the adequacy of our provision for income taxes.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Loss Contingencies We are regularly subject to claims, suits, government investigations, and other proceedings involving competition and antitrust, intellectual property, privacy, indirect taxes, labor and employment, commercial disputes, content generated by our users, goods and services offered by advertisers or publishers using our platforms, and other matters.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Certain of these matters include speculative claims for substantial or indeterminate amounts of damages.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We record a liability when we believe that it is probable that a loss has been incurred and the amount can be reasonably estimated.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If we determine that a loss is reasonably possible and the loss or range of loss can be estimated, we disclose the possible loss in the Notes to the Consolidated Financial Statements.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We evaluate, on a regular basis, developments in our legal matters that could affect the amount of liability that has been previously accrued, and the matters and related reasonably possible losses disclosed, and make adjustments and changes to our disclosures as appropriate.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Significant judgment is required to determine both likelihood of there being and the estimated amount of a loss related to such matters.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Until the final resolution of such matters, there may be an exposure to loss in excess of the amount recorded, and such amounts could be material.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Should any of our estimates and assumptions change or prove to have been incorrect, it could have a material impact on our business, consolidated financial position, results of operations, or cash flows.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: See Note 10 of Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements included in Item 8 of this Annual Report on Form 10-K for additional information regarding contingencies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Alphabet Inc.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Business Combinations We allocate the fair value of purchase consideration to the tangible assets acquired, liabilities assumed and intangible assets acquired based on their estimated fair values.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The excess of the fair value of purchase consideration over the fair values of these identifiable assets and liabilities is recorded as goodwill.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: When determining the fair values of assets acquired and liabilities assumed, management makes significant estimates and assumptions, especially with respect to intangible assets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Critical estimates in valuing certain intangible assets include but are not limited to future expected cash flows from customer relationships and acquired patents and developed technology and discount rates.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Management's estimates of fair value are based upon assumptions believed to be reasonable, but which are inherently uncertain and unpredictable and, as a result, actual results may differ from estimates.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Other estimates associated with the accounting for acquisitions may change as additional information becomes available regarding the assets acquired and liabilities assumed, as more fully discussed in Note 6 of Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements included in Item 8 of this Annual Report on Form 10-K.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Goodwill Goodwill is allocated to reporting units expected to benefit from the business combination.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We evaluate our reporting units when changes in our operating structure occur, and if necessary, reassign goodwill using a relative fair value allocation approach.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: We test goodwill for impairment at the reporting unit level at least annually, or more frequently if events or changes in circumstances indicate that the asset may be impaired.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Goodwill impairment tests require judgment, including the identification of reporting units, assignment of assets and liabilities to reporting units, assignment of goodwill to reporting units, and determination of the fair value of each reporting unit.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Long-lived Assets Long-lived assets, including property and equipment, long-term prepayments, and intangible assets, excluding goodwill, are reviewed for impairment whenever events or changes in circumstances indicate that the carrying amount of an asset may not be recoverable.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: The evaluation is performed at the lowest level of identifiable cash flows independent of other assets.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: An impairment loss would be recognized when estimated undiscounted future cash flows generated from the assets are less than their carrying amount.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Measurement of an impairment loss would be based on the excess of the carrying amount of the asset group over its fair value.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Impairment of Marketable and Non-Marketable Securities We periodically review our marketable and non-marketable securities for impairment.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If we conclude that any of these investments are impaired, we determine whether such impairment is other-than-temporary.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: Factors we consider to make such determination include the duration and severity of the impairment, the reason for the decline in value and the potential recovery period and our intent to sell.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: For marketable debt securities, we also consider whether (1) it is more likely than not that we will be required to sell the security before recovery of its amortized cost basis, and (2) the amortized cost basis cannot be recovered as a result of credit losses.

name: Alphabet Inc.
sentence: If any impairment is considered other-than-temporary, we will write down the asset to its fair value and record the corresponding charge as other income (expense), net.

sentence: Item 7A QUANTITATIVE AND QUALITATIVE DISCLOSURES ABOUT MARKET RISK We are exposed to financial market risks, including changes in currency exchange rates and interest rates.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: Foreign Currency Exchange Risk We transact business globally in multiple currencies.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: Our international revenues, as well as costs and expenses denominated in foreign currencies, expose us to the risk of fluctuations in foreign currency exchange rates against the U.S. dollar.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: We are a net receiver of foreign currencies and therefore benefit from a weakening of the U.S. dollar and are adversely affected by a strengthening of the U.S. dollar relative to the foreign currency.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: As of December 31, 2016, our most significant currency exposures are the British pound, Euro, and Japanese yen.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: In the fourth quarter of 2016, we began using foreign exchange forward contracts in addition to the existing foreign exchange option contracts, to protect our forecasted U.S. dollar-equivalent earnings from changes in foreign currency exchange rates.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: When the U.S. dollar strengthens, gains from foreign currency options and forwards reduce the foreign currency losses related to our earnings.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: When the U.S. dollar weakens, losses from foreign currency forwards offset the foreign currency gains related to our earnings.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: These hedging contracts reduce, but do not entirely eliminate, the impact of currency exchange rate movements.

name: Alphabet Inc.

sentence: We designate these contracts as cash flow hedges for accounting purposes.

sentence: We record spot-to-spot foreign currency exchange rate changes of these

sentence: contracts as a component of accumulated other comprehensive income (AOCI) and subsequently reclassify them into revenues to offset the hedged exposures as they occur.

sentence: We exclude the change in the time value and forward points of these contracts from our assessment of hedge effectiveness.

sentence: These excluded components are recognized in other income (expense), net.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: We considered the historical trends in currency exchange rates and determined that it was reasonably possible that changes in exchange rates of 10% could be experienced in the near term.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: If the U.S. dollar weakened by 10% as of December 31, 2015 and December 31, 2016, the amount recorded in AOCI reflecting spot-to-spot foreign currency rate changes related to our foreign exchange contracts before tax effect would have been approximately $221 million and $920 million lower as of December 31, 2015 and December 31, 2016, and the total amount of expense recorded as other income (expense), net, would have been approximately $203 million higher in the year ended December 31, 2015 and $14 million lower in the year ended December 31, 2016.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: If the U.S. dollar strengthened by 10% as of December 31, 2015 and December 31, 2016, the amount recorded in accumulated AOCI related to our foreign exchange contracts before tax effect would have been approximately $1.5 billion and $1.0 billion higher as of December 31, 2015 and December 31, 2016, and the total amount of expense recorded as other income (expense), net, would have been approximately $313 million and $13 million higher in the years ended December 31, 2015 and December 31, 2016.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: In both scenarios, the change in the value recorded in in AOCI would be expected to offset a corresponding foreign currency change in forecasted hedged revenues when recognized.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: In addition, we use foreign exchange forward contracts to offset the foreign exchange risk on our assets and liabilities denominated in currencies other than the local currency of the subsidiary.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: These forward contracts reduce, but do not entirely eliminate, the impact of currency exchange rate movements on our assets and liabilities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: The foreign currency gains and losses on the assets and liabilities are recorded in other income (expense), net, which are offset by the gains and losses on the forward contracts.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: We considered the historical trends in currency exchange rates and determined that it was reasonably possible that adverse changes in exchange rates of 10% for all currencies could be experienced in the near term.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: These reasonably possible adverse changes in exchange rates of 10% were applied to total monetary assets and liabilities denominated in currencies other than the local currencies at the balance sheet dates to compute the adverse impact these changes would have had on our income before income taxes in the near term.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: These changes would have resulted in an adverse impact on income before income taxes of approximately $61 million and $40 million as of December 31, 2015 and December 31, 2016.

name: Alphabet Inc.

sentence: The adverse impact as of December 31, 2015 and December 31, 2016 is after consideration of the offsetting effect of approximately $539 million and $554 million from foreign exchange contracts in place for the months of December 31, 2015 and December 31, 2016.

sentence: Interest Rate Risk Our investment strategy is to achieve a return that will allow us to preserve capital and maintain liquidity requirements.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: We invest primarily in debt securities including those of the U.S. government and its agencies, corporate debt securities, agency mortgage-backed securities, money market and other funds, municipal securities, time deposits, asset backed securities, and debt instruments issued by foreign governments.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: By policy, we limit the amount of credit exposure to any one issuer.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: Our investments in both fixed rate and floating rate interest earning securities carry a degree of interest rate risk.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: Fixed rate securities may have their fair market value adversely impacted due to a rise in interest rates, while floating rate securities may produce less income than predicted if interest rates fall.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: As of December 31, 2015 and December 31, 2016, unrealized losses on our marketable debt securities were primarily due to temporary interest rate fluctuations as a result of higher market interest rates compared to interest rates at the time of purchase.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: We account for both fixed and variable rate securities at fair value with changes on gains and losses recorded in AOCI until the securities are sold.

name: Alphabet Inc.
section_name: Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk
sentence: We use interest rate derivative contracts to hedge gains and losses on our securities.

name: Alphabet Inc.
